The paper focuses on pose estimation and tracking in videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves designing an end-to-end multi-task network (MTN) and utilizing feature pyramids, which are also common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of person re-identification (Re-ID), which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper addresses the practicality of the proposed method for real-world applications, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO).
